The evidence with the title 'Oxidative stress and neurodegenerative diseases: a review of ... ' says In-built antioxidant system of body plays its decisive role in prevention of any loss due to free radicals . However  ... Neural cells suffer functional or sensory loss in neurodegenerative diseases .  ... Antioxidants have a wide scope to sequester metal ions involved in neuronal plaque formation to prevent oxidative stress . 
